@database "System Information.Guide"

## This is a doc file in the amigaguide.library format. Hypertext should soon
## be available on the Amiga at system level, and since the .guide format is
## perfectly humanly readable, I prefer to distribute this doc file in the
## present form. I apologize for any inconvenience; I'm convinced that in the
## long run everybody will appreciate this choice (and anyway "there is still
## time to change the road you're on"...). If you have the amigaguide.library
## keep this file in the same directory as System Information, and press the
## HELP key to get the on-line help.(Not implemented yet, sorry) Being a non-
## registered developer I do not have access to the how-to's of doing this.
## If the help window doesn't appear, this means that amigaguide.library is
## not in the LIBS: directory, or the System Information.guide file (this one
## is not in the same directory as System Information. There is also a chance
## that you don't have enough memory.
##
## If you want to make this document humanly readable, just remove all @Node,
## @Endnode, as well as @{link <somename>} combinations. But please do NOT 
## distribute such a document. Doing so is a violation of copyright laws and
## will make you liable for prosecution before court. If, like me you are not
## a registered developer, try out the minguide program floating around BBS.
## This is basically a CLI version of a hypertext reader complete with its C
## source. It'll enable you to get an idea of what Hypertext is.

@width 77

